enhancements_ready() {\r\n404.     return Ok(json!({\r\n405.         \"status\": \"indexing\",\r\n406.         \"message\": \"Code intelligence is still initializing. Core task management tools are available. Try again in a few seconds.\"\r\n407.     }));\r\n408. }\r\n409. ```\r\n410. \r\n411. This is preferable to returning an error because:\r\n412. - The agent can proceed with non-code-graph work\r\n413. - The agent can retry the code tool after a short delay\r\n414. - No error propagation or retry logic needed in the MCP client\r\n415. \r\n416. #### 5. Update `_health` Response\r\n417. \r\n418. **File**: `src/daemon/ipc_server.rs:276-290`\r\n419. \r\n420. Enrich the health response to include phase information:\r\n421. \r\n422. ```rust\r\n423. \"_health\" => {\r\n424.     let snapshot = state.snapshot_workspace().await;\r\n425.     let status = if snapshot.is_some() { \"ready\" } else { \"starting\" };\r\n426.     let enhancements = state.enhancements_ready();\r\n427.     IpcResponse::success(\r\n428.         id,\r\n429.         json!({\r\n430.             \"status\": status,\r\n431.             \"enhancements_ready\": enhancements,\r\n432.             \"uptime_seconds\": state.uptime_seconds(),\r\n433.             \"workspace\": snapshot.map(|s| s.path),\r\n434.             \"active_connections\": state.active_connections(),\r\n435.         }),\r\n436.     )\r\n437. }\r\n438. ```\r\n439. \r\n440. The shim continues to check `status == \"ready\"` and ignores `enhancements_ready` — no shim changes needed. Diagnostic tools can use the richer response.\r\n441. \r\n442. #### 6. Update `get_workspace_status`\r\n443. \r\n444. **File**: `src/tools/lifecycle.rs`\r\n445. \r\n446. Add enhancement status to the workspace status response:\r\n447. \r\n448. ```rust\r\n449. pub struct WorkspaceStatus {\r\n450.     // ... existing fields ...\r\n451.     pub enhancements_ready: bool,    // Phase 2 complete?\r\n452.     pub code_graph: CodeGraphStats,  // populated after Phase 2\r\n453. }\r\n454. ```\r\n455. \r\n456. ### Edge Cases and Considerations\r\n457. \r\n458. 1. **Tool calls during Phase 2**: If an agent calls `map_code` during Phase 2 indexing, it gets a clear `\"indexing\"` status message rather than an error or empty results. The agent can retry or proceed with other work.\r\n459. \r\n460. 2. **`flush_state` during Phase 2**: The `flush_state` tool dehydrates the code graph to `.engram/code-graph/`. If called during Phase 2, it should either skip code graph dehydration (not yet loaded) or wait. Recommend: skip with a note in the response.\r\n461. \r\n462. 3. **`index_workspace` during Phase 2**: If Phase 2 is still loading the existing graph, a concurrent `index_workspace` call could conflict. Guard with `enhancements_ready()` check.\r\n463. \r\n464. 4. **Phase 2 failure modes**: If `hydrate_code_graph` fails (corrupt JSONL), the daemon stays running without code intelligence. If `backfill_embeddings` fails (model not available), same — core tools unaffected. Both are logged at WARN level.\r\n465. \r\n466. 5. **TTL timer placement**: The TTL idle timer should still start after Phase 1 (when \"ready\" fires), not after Phase 2. The daemon is usable after Phase 1; waiting for Phase 2 would delay the idle countdown unnecessarily on workspaces where code graph loading is slow.\r\n467. \r\n468. 6. **Backward compatibility**: The `_health` response adds `enhancements_ready` as a new optional field. Existing shims and MCP clients ignore unknown fields. The `\"ready\"` status semantics are unchanged — it still means \"daemon can serve tool calls.\"\r\n469. \r\n470. ### Files to Modify\r\n471. \r\n472. | File | Change |\r\n473. |------|--------|\r\n474. | `src/tools/lifecycle.rs` | Split `set_workspace` into `set_workspace_core` + `set_workspace_enhancements` |\r\n475. | `src/daemon/ipc_server.rs` | Update background `tokio::spawn` to call phases sequentially; update `_health` response |\r\n476. | `src/server/state.rs` | Add `enhancements_ready: AtomicBool` to `AppState` |\r\n477. | `src/tools/read.rs` | Guard `map_code`, `list_symbols`, `impact_analysis`, `unified_search`, `query_graph`, `get_collection_context` with `enhancements_ready()` check |\r\n478. | `src/tools/write.rs` | Guard `index_workspace`, `sync_workspace`, `link_task_to_code`, `unlink_task_from_code` with `enhancements_ready()` check |\r\n479. | `src/tools/mod.rs` | No changes needed (dispatch is unchanged) |\r\n480. | `tests/integration/smoke_test.rs` | Update to verify Phase 1 returns \"ready\" before Phase 2 completes |\r\n481. \r\n482. ### Verification Criteria\r\n483. \r\n484. - [ ] Daemon reports `\"ready\"` within 3 seconds of startup on a workspace with 100+ code files\r\n485. - [ ] Core task management tools (`create_task`, `get_task_graph`, `flush_state`) work immediately after \"ready\"\r\n486. - [ ] Code graph tools (`map_code`, `list_symbols`) return `\"indexing\"` status during Phase 2\r\n487. - [ ] Code graph tools return full results after Phase 2 completes\r\n488. - [ ] `get_workspace_status` includes `enhancements_ready` field\r\n489. - [ ] Phase 2 failure does not crash the daemon or affect core tools\r\n490. - [ ] TTL idle timer starts after Phase 1, not Phase 2\r\n491. - [ ] All existing smoke/integration tests pass\r\n492. - [ ] No regression in `_health` / `check_health` / `poll_until_ready` behavior\r\n493. \r\n494. ### References\r\n495. \r\n496. - Current `set_workspace`: `src/tools/lifecycle.rs:57-117`\r\n497. - Background spawn: `src/daemon/ipc_server.rs:401-437`\r\n498. - `_health` handler: `src/daemon/ipc_server.rs:276-290`\r\n499. - Shim polling: `src/shim/lifecycle.rs:56-82` (`check_health`), `156-183` (`poll_until_ready`)\r\n500. - `AppState`: `src/server/state.rs:30-39` (`WorkspaceSnapshot`), `151-170` (`snapshot_workspace`, `set_workspace`)\r\n501. - Tool dispatch: `src/tools/mod.rs:60-115`\r\n502. - Code graph tools: `src/tools/read.rs:474-530` (`map_code`), `620-680` (`list_symbols`), `1130-1170` 